<HL> Business Brief: Placer Dome Inc. </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<CO> PDG T.KGM T.S </CO>
<IN> TNM </IN>
<TEXT>
   Placer Dome Inc. said it agreed in principal to acquire all the shares it doesn't own of two subsidiaries, Kiena Gold Mines Ltd. and Sigma Mines (Quebec) Ltd. 

   The Toronto gold-mining concern said the agreement calls for minority holders to receive 0.97 Placer Dome common share for each of 2,890,512 shares of Sigma and 0.92 share for each of 5,091,290 shares of Kiena, giving the combined transactions an indicated value of $94.5 million. 

   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Placer Dome closed at $12.625 a share, down 12.5 cents. 
In Toronto Stock Exchange trading, Kiena closed at 14.25 Canadian dollars a share ($11.52), up 1.50 dollars. 
Sigma closed at 14 dollars Monday and didn't trade yesterday. 

   Placer Dome already owns 64.7% of Sigma and 56.7% of Kiena, which are based in Toronto and operate gold mines near Val d'Or, Quebec. 

   Shareholders of the two subsidiaries are to vote on the plan June 15. 
The units initially will operate as separate, wholly owned subsidiaries, with combined gold output this year estimated at 130,000 ounces. 

